
•	What it is: Git is a distributed version control system. It helps developers track changes to their code, collaborate with others, and manage different versions of their projects.
•	Purpose: The main purpose of Git is to manage the history of changes in a codebase, allowing multiple people to work on the same project without overwriting each other’s work. It provides tools for branching and merging code, reviewing history, and managing changes.
GitHub
•	What it is: GitHub is a web-based platform that hosts Git repositories. It provides a user-friendly interface to manage Git repositories, collaborate with other developers, and perform code reviews. It also offers additional features like issue tracking, pull requests, and project management tools.
•	Purpose: The main purpose of GitHub is to facilitate collaboration and sharing of code. It makes it easy to manage Git repositories online, collaborate with others, and contribute to open-source projects. GitHub also integrates with various other tools and services to enhance the development workflow.
